reviews.text:
They charge about 5400 dollars per course for international students, you will need to pay at least 172,800 dollars tuition fee if you want to get a four-year honour degree here.
However it’s still a reasonable price for world class universities and the academic reputation here is one of the best in Australia.
Beautiful campus either for study or visit as a tourist attraction. In the spring the whole place turns purple. It has a variety of shops for having a coffee or some food.

This place is wonderful, I love this place very much and hope that it will be always open! Suggested to people who love this shop, please visit it! Its an experience that cant be missed! This shop is open most of the days so if you have time, just drop by to help them.

Beautiful campus, helpful staff, high quality teaching. Highly accessible by bus or ferry. Beautiful places to walk or jog. Great sports facilities. Great food and coffee options. The library spaces are plentiful and well maintained. I've loved my time here and look forward to my next few years as a postgrad here too!!

Excellent university with top notch facilities and  professors. One of the top universities in the world and ranked 1st in Queensland. Astonishing and beautiful campus. This 20th century university or stand stone university has lot to offer. Currently, I'm studying master's degree and the experience is really good.

Terrific snapshot of Brisbane's history. Very good static displays, easy access. Being in the city, parking is a premium in both spaces and pricing. Historical society of Qld is also based here. Very friendly staff and great resources.
Absolutely gorgeous people there, very knowledgeable and super friendly
The staff were very friendly and knowledgeable, the place is very good.

We were a little disappointed with this museum as, like a previous reviewer had commented, there is a lot of reading to be done and some articles/facts were repeated as you went on. We were wowed by other museums that were free entry so maybe expected too much from this one which has admission fees? Also the museum seemed a bit patchy and disjointed with no strong theme running from start to end.

A good place to learn about Brisbane's history. You're rather forced to have a guide, but it turns out to be very useful - you learn significantly more than if you were just wandering around and looking at the exhibits. The museum has a bit of a ramshackle feel at times, but is all the better for being a little less polished than some of the alternatives. This is a must for anyone wanting to learn about Brisbane's past.

Just as it says, General Douglas MacArthur's HQ in our own Brisbane. Great volunteer staff who greet you and guide you to MacArthur"s office/museum and very helpful and informative. Good information, videos and displays of the war and of course MacArthur's office itself. Walk where MacArthur walked and worked during this terrible time in our history and feel the history and perhaps the man's presence from a time past.
Good place, I'll come back.
It's  cool but a little boring  and way to boring for small children
Very interesting

Easy to get to from central train station if you come in on the train, only $5 entry on a concession ticket, and a great place to learn about the history of Australia in the pacific theatre in World War II as well as Korea

Nice place to spend a few hours stepping back in time and learning about some of the great things that have happened in the past during war or ocean exploring and sailing like the pink lady. The older guides are great and passionate in giving out information. Had fun 
⛵🚢🛥⛴🛳🚤🛶
Great to walk around again for the first time in 30 years. My 5 year old daughter loved it.

Amaazing place. A lot of things to see. A bit pricey though. Its $16 for an adult and $7 for child over 5 and under 13.

The war ship is in its original condition with many old mattresses, ropes still intact and kept inside. 

As the ship is not restored or preserved, it looks like its parked in the junk yard rather than in the museum. It should be maintained or atleast be painted to take off the rust and make it more appealing to the crowd. 

All being said, I still liked the overall experience as we could see many small chambers in their original shape. I have never seen the anchor room before and was amazed to see the width and length of the rope.

The museum at back had lots of items to explore.

PS: the ship is all metal and being on sunny side of Brisbane river it gets heated up fast. There are couple of pedestal fans but they can only do as much.

Great collection of Australian maritime artifacts, both recent and old including a heritage listed dry dock, World War II warship, tugboat and record breaking sailboat. A great lighthouse exhibit and many interactive exhibits - so much more. Very knowledgeable and friendly  staff.
A huge range of amazing things to see good for all the family.

A super interesting visit with something for everyone of all ages. The museum is free entry and can keep you entertained for hours. So much to read with different topics on each floor. I personally found this place especially interesting as it is very focussed on Australian/ Queensland wildlife which is great for visitors and children alike. Unfortunately they were still in the process of constructing the space exhibition but I would definitely love to return to see it.

Well, first of all it is free and a great place for all ages. Kids are catered for with lots of dinosaur stuff as well as plenty of interactive activities, which change regularly. There are some real Aussie items here that are very exciting such as material from Bligh's ship. Buses are across the road and the ferry is just a step away. I would suggest that visitors park somewhere else in Brisbane and catch the bus or ferry to South Bank.

Awesome experience, not just for the kids.  PAID EXHIBITS WELL WORTH IT! Have fun!
Spark lab rocked, well done to museum staff. Credit to you for the wonderful atmosphere you create.

Very lovely place to take every member of the family. They had a lot of exciting science exhibits on display. Very knowledgeable staff, especially those responsible for explaining the planets and chemical reaction. There was a lot to see and do and it was value for time and money. It's great to have an annual pass if you want to be able to come whenever you want. There are other places to go and to see while there. It was a refreshing experience.

I love this museum so much! Definitely one of my favourite national museums in Australia. It’s very well designed and great to look at. They often have fantastic exhibitions to check out, a must see if you’re in Brisbane.

A super interesting visit with something for everyone of all ages. The museum is free entry and can keep you entertained for hours. So much to read with different topics on each floor. I personally found this place especially interesting as it is very focussed on Australian/ Queensland wildlife which is great for visitors and children alike. Unfortunately they were still in the process of constructing the space exhibition but I would definitely love to return to see it.

There are some real Aussie items here that are very exciting such as material from Bligh's ship. Buses are across the road and the ferry is just a step away. I would suggest that visitors park somewhere else in Brisbane and catch the bus or ferry to South Bank.

Very knowledgeable staff, especially those responsible for explaining the planets and chemical reaction. There was a lot to see and do and it was value for time and money. It's great to have an annual pass if you want to be able to come whenever you want. There are other places to go and to see while there. It was a refreshing experience.

I love this museum so much! Definitely one of my favourite national museums in Australia. It’s very well designed and great to look at. They often have fantastic exhibitions to check out, a must see if you’re in Brisbane.

We were drawn to this Gallery for its aboriginal art collections which were very interesting, particularly the ceramics. The Gallery forms part of a complex with the Library and Modern Art Gallery. Access is free and the collections are quite good. We were taken with one mini gallery which is based on a painting titled Under the Jacarunda Tree. After this visit, we went immediately to the Botanical Gardens to see a tree in bloom! We recommend a visit.

Clean well organised good  lighting quiet and helpfully staff
Plenty of paintings pottery(some really beautiful things) plenty of seating to sit and look. The old classic paintings are the best to really look at.  It looks like there are a lot of things for kids above5. Just go in for a wander you will enjoy an relax.

Always have great content available with some intriguing displays. Great historical content with some modern Australian artworks being featured at time. Sometimes they have massive sections closed due to new exhibitions so be sure to check the website to ensure you are disappointed with closures as we have been in the past. Staff are relatively friendly most of the time.
Great place to enjoy the best Australia has to offer! Easy to while away a few hours. A great respite from the hustle and bustle of the city. Easy access to public transport too!

My daughters and myself went to the beautiful yoga session yesterday evening with a friend. It was wonderful. A real privilege to look around during the session at incredible Australian art. We loved it.

Wonderful place to view all of Australia's wildlife. First visited here 18 years ago and just been back. Glad to say it is still as good as ever. Definitely THE place to have a photo with a koala - not rushed and personal opportunities for photos with your own phone also. Enjoyed the sheepdog demonstration, bird of prey show and kangaroo feeding. Well worth a visit.

Great place. Lots of koalas. Wife really loved it. Easy to get to. Recommend coming early in the day so you can make the most of the $38 per adult and do the cruise and sheep dog and farm animals. We only spent 2 hours but I think coming earlier is better especially if you have kids. Staff are nice always off to take pics. Nice place.

I GOT TO HOLD A KOALA!!! OK, that should be enough for anyone to want to visit, but it only gets better!  There's the Kangaroo enclosure where you can feed and pet the kangaroos and Emus.  They're pretty chill and used to people and kids so its a lot of fun to just go and pet them all!  

Be sure to go around and watch the feeding times as the zookeepers do a great job explaining all about the animals.  

Overall a great place... and yes, we don't even live in Australia yet and my wife and I already have annual passes.

My toddler loves coming here. So many animals to see, kangaroos to feed, and animal shows. We have an annual pass which also gives us great discounts (even if you only use it twice it's worth it). Some favourites are the platypus, reptile enclosure, barn animals... Actually there is nothing that isn't a favourite. Totally worth a visit if not a regular activity.

Great wildlife sanctuary (they've got more than koalas obviously). Animals galore! Very family friendly, with plenty of shows to go and watch. Great for feeding kangaroos and taking pictures with koalas. Well worth the money!

A huge open park & garden available for family and friends barbecues! Public facilities provided! Parking provided! A great atmosphere suitable for relaxing in a quiet space! Great for group events! Or personal quiet time! Flowers are maintained & replaced regularly! Huge shady trees to read a book under or have a picnic! Food & coffee vans are available plus parking! Wheelchair access is available. The park goes right down to the water! Great scenery & a peaceful atmosphere! Plenty of barbeque facilities provided as long as you clean it after you have finished!
Beautiful place. Very well kept and a variety of flowers in bloom. Good and well marked Parkrun course by the river. Great little play area for kids. Parking can be limited.

Australia Day and New Farm Park mixed well for me. Lots of Aussies enjoying the day... Loved to see it. New Farm Park's Beautiful Gardens are worth the visit. It is unlike other parks that I visited in Brisbane. Good place for a Day out. Grab your foods, Books and enjoy the day.
Love this park. Best playground for kids in Brisbane, beautiful flower gardens, picnic facilities at the riverside and all that the Powerhouse has to offer within. Public space perfection

Lots of play equipment and large area for kids to be kids. Huge ground available for picnics and benches around the park. While lots of parking is available but due to its popularity finding a park can become a luck and patience game 😁. Still highly recommend it.

It's a great Fun out here. Lovely air. I literally hadn't been yo Harbour and seeing these many ships was just unbelievable. There are places to sit, fish, click some photos. Restaurants and Bars nearby also has plenty to offer for the visitors out here. Good enough place overall for nature lovers.
View that you shouldn’t miss at manly beach lots of cafe play ground for kids good ambience and very relaxing views

Jetty is a great place for a stroll. Have a coffee at the cafe at the end or just admire the millions of dollars worth of boats in the harbor.
You can also fish off the harbor rock walls near the entrance as there's lots of bream around especially at night.
Funny the water
Great little village shops. Groceries , coffee shops and restaurants.
Good platform for any performance, has shady place  to sit and relax.
A little bit disappointed with snow4kids. Thought would be a good fun for my daughter but the lack of attractions change my mind. 😤

I performed there with the raise your voice festival. Its beautiful just need better seats, the ones there are very poor quality like even just having a long bench for people to sit down would be good instead of individual seats that fold up when youre not sitting on them
Awesome place for the seminar that we watched, reminded me of the University halls.
Lots of fascility. Everything available for families fun day out.

Very clean and well maintained.  The staff are really friendly and knowledgeable about the store and their products.  Saturday’s are crazy busy, I was still able to checkout quickly and easily.  Keep up the good work!

I love coming to this place to look at all the fruit and vegetables, meat and baked goods, and seafood. Such a good range and great quality! Of course, it is very expensive because it's Brisbane but nice to have once in a while! There's different cereals and jams, cheeses, yogurts, all different things to tale home to try! Aesthetically pleasing as well so take all the time you want for a wander.
I love it always a good vibe friendly staff clean neat and tidy good fruit and vegetables beautiful flowers highly recommend cheers Lynda Clark hairdresser
Super expensive chain stores but nice high end little food market that one can find more challenging items at.
A street frequented by fashion people There are many unique editing shops and cafes.

Friendly service and deliciously fresh coffee. I come back to refill my canister of beans (you get a discount if you re-use!) and am always greeted with extremely friendly staff. A great little place to re-stock or have a sit-down coffee.
Iced latte was excellent. Cappuccino could have been hotter. Would go back. They flip u for a free coffee! Novel. Seating is a bit old fashioned.
My coffee from Merlo is always perfect. They make great iced lattes and chai lattes. Staff are always very friendly and the wait times aren't too long during peak hours.
Super quick service, delicious coffee, 'nuff said.
1/3/2019 - Merlo Cafe on Queen Street. One of the best around serving my favourite Long Black to go with my breakfast burrito.

Tasty burgers, good deal for your money and laid back environment. Location is very convenient and fast service. Quite different from other burger places. During my visit they were missing couple of things on their menu, due to previous busy night. I think they should improve their efficiency to deliver consitent availability of products they sell.

Mos Burger is like a Japanese version of McDonald's. Super yummy wagu beef burger with perfectly cooked chips! The wedges were a bit disappointing in comparison to the chips, and there wasn't enough sauce for all the chips and wedges. However, the ice tea we had was delicious, and I would come back again just for the ice tea.
Consistently good customer service. Staff are always so friendly. Tasty, high quality food. Love coming here for lunch whenever I'm in the city.
Really sad to see only 2 vegetarian options on the menu hence the 4 star rating. But if purely based on price, staff and shop, then it'd be a 5. Really tasty and affordable food.

If you're a vegan looking for a quick high quality bite to eat this is your place - order the Veggie Croquette without the mayo! For $5 is it such good value. Fresh, crispy and very tasty, The barbecue sauce has great flavour and compliments the vege patty really well. Staff are really friendly and have an upbeat attitude. Love how there is also the traditional floor seating. Only negative I can comment on is the paper / excess waste used to wrap the burger and that the size of the burger is smaller than average. If you have a big appetite you'll might want to order a side dish.

The pancakes are always amazing. If your want consistently amazing pancakes this is the place to go. Depending on the time and day you visit it may be wise to book a table. The wait can be long but if you have the time then it’s worth it. I had the short stack of two buttermilk pancakes with ice cream and an almond milk flat white. Just writing this review is making me want to go back again.

A bit of a wait for food, but fantastic fluffy pancakes at a great price, complete with your choice of ice cream, fruits, and other extras. I was blown away by how cheap the meals were and how customizable they are. Great drinks menu, also at a good price. And a beautiful atmosphere nestled in a quaint old church with friendly enough staff.

This is the perfect place If you are in search of pancakes, sweet or savory ones. They have a huge variety of them. You can also pick a menu where you have one savoury pancake and one sweet one. They serve the savoury ones with salad on a side.

Big portions, tasty and great service. Good location, in the center of Brisbane . The local is different and that gives a plus to it.

This was once a Cathedral built in 1904, it was turned into a Pancake restaurant in the 1960's. It is beautiful!!!! They have gluten free options on almost the entire menu. Friendly staff and centrally located.

Amazing location, in an old church. The staff is kind, and the place is almost always crowded. Discount if you are student, which is pretty good as the prices are a little high. Nice place where to eat pancakes or milkshakes - the quality has recently improved. Overall, a must-try place. You don't come here only for the food, but for the experience of eating in an old church!

had a birthday dinner here last year in august! food was delicious but slightly overpriced :-( the service was very very impressive and the staff made my family and i feel very welcomed! they also offered to place the birthday cake in the kitchen while we were having our dinner and brought it out after dessert with a lighted candle!

will definitely be back again! thank you!

Food’s presentations are very lovely with good taste. We ordered the lunch set, which is worth the money as we got 3 or 4 starters and 1 main with rice and miso soup and also the lovely dessert. But the drinks and alcohol are kind of overpriced... 

The vibe is also nice (suitable for couples).

Had a wonderful anniversary dinner last night at Sono Portside. The management and staff were truly exceptional, particularly the wait staff for our table. She was friendly, courteous, patient, prompt and knowledgeable. The food was excellent and we did not have to wait long. A good team, a great restaurant. We had a great time.

Thank you.
Sharon & Ed Low
Authentic Japanese restaurant with excellent food. A bit pricey but worth it. A definite recommend

Big thanks to the team at Aria for a splendid evening. Waterfront dining at it's finest with friendly staff, wonderful wines and seasonal menus. Food was superb and the experience was memorable. It's understated elegance with a warm feel.

My husband surprised me for my birthday. Dinner booked for 6.30 to 8.30 which gave us plenty of time to enjoy our meal. Did not feel rushed either. 

They accommodated us with a table for 2 close to the window with a view of Brisbane River. 

From the first appetizer to end, the food was truly amazing! All seasoned so no need for salt and pepper. Wine list had plenty of Australia wines to choose from. Bread was from a local bakery in Tenneriffe. 

All in all we had a great night with great food & perfect service. I would recommend Aria Brisbane. Treat yourself & enjoy!

Great service, but we had the 7 course tasting menu, and unfortunately most dishes were disappointing. In particular, the tuna was completely flavourless and the prawn was dry and lacked flavour despite excellent accompanying sides and sauces. None of the dishes had a strong impact on us, except the chuck tail which was fantastic, and the dessert.
Amazing place. Steak was absolutely amazing. Plus they even did a great celebration for a birthday! Service was amazing and food was well worth the price! Hopefully will come back here soon.

Disappointing experience!

The location is perfect, with view on the Brisbane river and the Storey Bridge. The interior is cosy and well designed.

The service staff were rather cold, they did their job and brought us plates, filled in the water and wine. However, it felt like we were an inconvenience and to be honest it is the first time this happened in a restaurant of this standard.

The food was interesting, however some flavours were clashing in the mouth and one flavour would overpower the other one resulting in not tasting the weaker flavour any more. An example is with the Snapper, the fish had a very delicate taste that could have been brought to life with some well-chosen ingredients. However, in this instance there was the pickled daikon and given its strong flavour, blanketed the flavour of the fish completely.

The last comment would be in regard to the 1985 port - which came with 1/5 of sediments in my class and all around it. I didn't notice the sediments in my glass until it became evident that a dark and murky substance was lying at the bottom.

It was for a special occasion that we went to Aria and for a restaurant of this standard, I was expecting better service and better food.

I thought this was a great restaurant and the food was delicious. They are a little out of the way but the views and food are worth it. Staff were very attentive but not overpowering. Excellent venue for that special occasion. Don’t expect a cheap night though, however the cost is expected for such good quality with a very innovative menu.

My fiancée and I celebrated our 4th anniversary and recent engagement at Alchemy. The ambience was great and we managed to get a table with a view of the story bridge (absolutely stunning at night!). Our waitress, Morgan, made us feel very welcome and was very attentive to us throughout the evening. The food was exceptional! Everything from the presentation to the combination of flavours and textures was beautiful. We want to thank the chef and staff at Alchemy for making our evening such a special one.

Attended as part of a set menu day/business function. Staff presented well and were polite, attentive and helpful. 

Food was adventurous yet basic enough for every tastebud to enjoy. Extensive drinks list to mull over.

And if you were boring and for some reason weren't impressed by the restaurants other great features, the view is always spectacular!
Great quality meals. Great customer service. 11 dollars for still mineral water bottle was a bit much though. My medium rare steak was cooked to perfection. Cocktails were yummy but super small :)

Service from our waitress Lilly was great. French speaking, petite and helpful. The food for me was the disappointment. While the vegetarian menu seemed appealing, my selections from it were underwhelming. The gnocchi were more like pasta shells than any gnocchi I have encountered and not flavoursome either. On the basis of that alone I would have given 3 stars but my colleagues enjoyed their beeftarian dishes so on that basis and the service it gets the 4th star. The location i s good, no doubt. The decor is pleasant.
Excellent food and service. Good ambience if a bit business oriented. Would have liked a little more non meat choice but what we had was very good. Server Yolanda charming and efficient. Recommended.

Have been coming here annually for a while! Always amazing steaks. Exceptional service and a lovely location. Highly recommend. Staff are more than happy to walk you through a detailed description of menu (including cuts of steak).

An interesting and unique menu. Steaks are of  high quality and meals elegantly  prepared. Wait staff are very helpful and have good knowledge of the menu

After visiting here a second time I found the waiter took significant amounts of time to tend to us (I shouldn't have to wait 20 mins to place an order).I also noted the tables around us had more frequent service.

Terrible service. My friend and I were seated under strong air conditioner, I told the server my friend was shivering and asked if we could change seat. The server was reluctant to arrange a better seating, but simply told us other tables were booked. We were there for less than two hours and during that time there plenty of empty seat. He could have arranged us to a better seat instead of having us eating in cold. No one came to ask us if we were satisfied with food. No checking with customer satisfaction when we checked out either. The wait of food was long as other reviewers complained. I will NEVER go to this restaurant again.

Great steak, one of the best. 
However this place needs a refurb / upgrade and some energy and ambience. 
The vibe was low. 
I felt like I was stuck in an 80’s reception venue.

Fantastic service - a  quality cut you will not find at many places in Brisbane. These guys are pros at fades, with amazing clipper work and very handy with the scissors. First haircut I've walked out of genuinely impressed and received several compliments from the shop to home. If you're looking for a fresh chop, do yourself a favour and make an appointment. Cheers Jordan!
Had my hair dyed for the first time. Can't be happier than this. I feel 10 years younger! Kudos to talented and friendly Lorraine.

It's rare to come across a barber with such depth of knowledge. Jordan definitely knows how to cut hair according to different head shapes and with a diverse range skills. Cool dude too.

Would recommend! 👍👍
Jordan paid exceptional attention to detail and care. He explained everything perfectly and showed great technical skills. Highly recommend him to anyone wanting a quality cut.

If i could kiss Jordan and not be arrested i would. 
By far the best place in town for a haircut, shave or hair highlight. 
Have never once felt like i was being rushed out or that my requests were unreasonable.
Service is top notch.
Thanks Mark & Jordan for all the free laughs and always making me feel welcomed.

Exceptional food and service. Although it was busy, it was quiet enough to enjoy conversation. Enjoyable to watch the staff and owner, meticulous attention to detail and a genuine enjoyment in their work. Will be back. Thank you for a wonderful meal!

Had dinner here with my mom on a busy Saturday night. Lots of tasty tapas. Service was friendly. Food was good. Will return to try more dishes. We hosted a large corporate event at Moda. I was so happy with the support Moda supplied. The event was smooth easy and Juliette, Francois and the staff were just incredible. Thank you so much for contributing so much to such a successful evening.
Thank you for an outstanding wedding reception. The best food ever at a wedding, attentive staff and such a wonderful venue. Peter and Sue Freeman
Love the new location. Food is great service was excellent. The menu is ideal for sharing tapas plates through to main meals. Can’t wait to go back and try things that we didn’t choose this time.
Nice food . Funny mix of staff. Mainly not Spanish. In any case worth visiting for tasting something different and getting great attention from the personnel.
Great Sushi! It's on the higher end of price but the quality is great. The Uni (Sea Urchin) sushi is super plump and fresh. Service has always been great too.

We decided to spontaneously go to Sake for a friends birthday dinner this week. We had all been quite often and normally the staff, food and atmosphere is great. This time however the staff would hardly look you in the eye when you were talking to them. We were sat at a table where the roof was dripping water and we had to start moving ourselves before they even tried to assist. They then didn’t put any sign for safety or cloth down where it had been dripping. The food was good however we were not given the correct amount. One dish we got didn’t have as many pieces as we had ordered and the other dish they gave us twice as many as we first ordered. When advising staff of issues they would apologise with no look of actual empathy and instead would avoid us and talk to each other about the issues instead of providing us with an actual apology regarding the lack of service. My father can go to Sake at least two times a week and often brings clients and he has advised this is the second time in 3 weeks the service has been horrible and he will be dropping back his business with the restaurant.
Expensive restaurant. We had a set menu. The timing is good. The rose wine is perfect. The views are great. Not 5 stars for me because of value/money balance.

Seriously this was some of the best food I've eaten in years, and I've had a great couple of food years. Also the customer service was above and beyond. A great experience, would take a lot of convincing for me to not take anyone back.
:) It was not a dinner, it was an experience!! The first time I tried sashimi and it was scrumptious! They have flavorful food and the staff really add value to the restaurant 😊

Excellent degustation. 7 course with additional surprises. Every dish worked fantastically well. Service top notch. Urbane is truly world class. Up there with the best meals I’ve had in New York, London and Sydney. I will definitely be returning.

Very good rare steak. Now I truly believe Australia has good beef! Recommend to all visitors to Bris. Good service. Great food with a difference. Good selection of wine. Friendly efficient staff. The whole experience was wonderful. A very different eating experience. Don’t expect standard fair. You will get subtle, exquisite flavours, amazing presentation and very attentive staff. The wine list is extensive and the decor conducive to long intimate conversations. Well worth the $$$$ for a special evening.

Good view of the city while enjoying a meal. At first i thought the restaurant would spin super fast, but when i actually went there it was turning really slow which was good. The view keeps changing as you eat your meal. Really good if you go in the evening as the city is all lit up and it looks good as. The food is yummy and the servers are super friendly. Recommend going here..!!!

This is one of my favorite places in the area. The dishes that they serve are amazing! The chef also knows how to interact with the customers. I have to say that this place deserves a 5-star rating from its clients.

Wonderful Place- great staff, attentive but not overwhelming.  Food was stunningly served & Also cooked perfectly. Flavors, textures, colour all considered and blended in a potpourri of bliss. Would have no hesitation in recommending & going again.  Thank you.
Really outstanding meal.  The cuttlefish was out of this world.  Lovely ambience.  We ate in their side room, which could use a bit of sound dampening interventions, but a great time nonetheless.
Service excellent but let down by chef. Sourdough was burnt and inedible. Cheese platter interesting an tasty but wildly overpriced.

On a recent trip late afternoon, we were told that our voices were too loud. 
Food quality good , pity about the attitude of owner/manager.
The cafe was only around a quarter full. 
Don't worry we won't be returning any time soon.
The Continental is such a special place! Their food nourishes the soul and their staff go above and beyond!
If you want to step up a level from the regular standard of food this is the place to go. Cooked by a chef rather than a line cook ingredients are fresh and the taste is divine.

An excellent music venue for live bands & a place to rub shoulders with other performing artists after their own gigs! Great breakfasts & meals all round! Wheelchair access is available & their own restroom! A great event venue!

The bartender painstakingly made me a really delicious cocktail last night, he even hand squeezed the lemon juice ❤️ Always a great time here. Go explore the out back seat in area, decorated with a beautiful mural, string lights and a.. washing line? If it’s your thing like mine, you’ll love it.
Great place to see musical acts. The front Bar is cosy and great to feel immersed in the music. The back room is more spacious and relaxed.

Love rics!
Best place to chill with a Delicious cocktail and a cigarette in your hand , whilst sitting in their backyard ♡

Absolutely awful management. The manager there with the big nose needs to stop being so power hungry and starting fights with patrons. Never have I been treated so disgustingly by someone. The place would improve immensely if she was fired, it's long overdue and word of mouth spreads.

Food overpriced for the meal size. The potato rosti and corn. Nothing goes well together for that meal. The staff were unable to work out how to split bill three ways. Added without authority extra so we all paid more each to make the maths easier. Then refunded coins. 
Ridiculous... won’t be back
Absolutely incredible service!!! Kathy & Grant were a dream team... will definitely be back! Great food, atmosphere and service :)
I thought the food was underwhelming and quite expensive for what it was. In terms of flavour, ingredients and presentation- they’ve missed the mark. The venue was lovely and staff was great though.

Coffee was good but poor service
We came in for a light breakfast and got directed to find our own table. It then took them so long to provide menus that we missed the window for the breakfast so we decided to just get coffees.
Shortly after this we were queried as to why we were sitting where we were and directed to find another table on our own. They then lost track of our order were we had to return to the front counter to get our order.
Fantastic food at a very reasonable price. Very tidy venue also. Clean and pleasant

Very clean and well maintained.  The staff are really friendly and knowledgeable about the store and their products.  Saturday’s are crazy busy, I was still able to checkout quickly and easily.  Keep up the good work!

I love coming to this place to look at all the fruit and vegetables, meat and baked goods, and seafood. Such a good range and great quality! Of course, it is very expensive because it's Brisbane but nice to have once in a while! There's different cereals and jams, cheeses, yogurts, all different things to tale home to try! Aesthetically pleasing as well so take all the time you want for a wander.
I love it always a good vibe friendly staff clean neat and tidy good fruit and vegetables beautiful flowers highly recommend cheers Lynda Clark hairdresser
Super expensive chain stores but nice high end little food market that one can find more challenging items at.
A street frequented by fashion people There are many unique editing shops and cafes.

Was seated outdoors at a comfy spot, blue light on table is really pretty and helpful. Wait staff was helpful and patient. Food came pretty quickly, and everything was delicious.
Got the antipasto platter, pumpkin pizza, and beef ribs to be shared between 4 adults, everyone was full and happy, and it was only $88 dollars.

Highly recommended, and would personally visit again.

Finally, a place that sells gourmet food that's filling! It looks good, it tastes good, and it's served at a decent size.
Lovely staff and an all around great vibe - it's like stepping into another world.

I went to the Mecca Bah tonight after work for dinner with some colleagues. All of our meals were delicious with lovely flavours.  Staff were very friendly and hospitable. Not even a grumble when we wanted to pay separately.  Will definitely be returning.
Food was amazing. Had the short beef ribs and trio of dips with Turkish bread. Ribs were tender and juicy and bread was fresh! So good, service was also polite and friendly. Will definitely be back!
Good vibes and nice service, but the food is what really brings it home! So good you'll want to chew it slowly and savour every bite. Just really really well made deliciousness.

They Lie to me NO Vegan Option & Waiting  There for Nothing waste of time at the Table. I Did NOT Like What Was on The Menu & it was Disgusting. So I left quick. I Did not want to be Seen There Either. Because I'm kinda famous. Definitely Not My Type Of Place.

I am vegan and one of my friends who went with me eats halal (my friend enjoyed the lamb). We loved the food and the experience so much that we came back the next night also. The staff and owners are very nice. Next time I am back in Albuquerque I will eat here again.

My favorite Indian food lunch buffet here in Albuquerque.  We make it a point to go meet at least once a month with our friends.  They have all the great stuff you'd expect at a Indian food buffet and they do a great job at all of it.  It's typically bustling and busy at lunch, but with several dining areas and attentive polite staff that are constantly on top of everything, it's always a pleasurable experience.

First time coming here, and first time eating Indian food, and I have to say that I loved it! The location is pretty old and might be in need for an update, but they make up for it with the great food. I went for lunch, and they have their buffet, which makes it really easy to get a sample of their offerings
Always wonderful!  Have been a patron for years, and it's always a good bet.  Had the baked eggplant and lamb meatballs.....great!  Always have an appetizer.

It's a great place whether on your own or large groups. Good value for money, but not the best Turkish cuisine, still yummy. Popular place, nice in and outside. OK wine options. Good vegetarian options. Kid friendly, family oriented. Overall a great restaurant.

Valentine's day... very very busy night. A table was held for me to be able to take my 1yr old and my wife 28weeks pregnant with twins.
I can't thank the manager, Jason I believe and our waiter to take 65 I think it was. We were served promptly and everyone around us was all smiles and the vibe of the restaurant was really warm and welcoming.  It's very hard for us to get out of the house much, thing as they are... so making our night special with great food and great service was very appreciated.
I recommend Ahmet's... made our one night out in a very long time pretty special.

I started going here when it first opened,  I haven't been back in years, went for dinner. Where is the Turkish gone?
It is a glorified kebab shop, but my local dose better. The meet was dry and bland.
The atmosphere, where has it gone? Kenny G style music,  where's the Turkish music gone? Where has the staff outfits gone?
Rather go to your local kebab shop don't waist your money or time.

Shocking service. The managers were very rude and so cramped the waiters couldn't even serve the food properly. Staff were rude and just didn't have the time to look at you. Quick to take your money. Not so quick with service. Will not be going there again. 
Food is not authenticate at all. Compared to other Turkish Restaurants. cannot compare.
Food was amazing - seating was tight for big crew. Belly dancer and musicians were superb. Highly recommend for large gatherings.

As Toowong locals,  we eat at Green Paw Paw on a regular basis and absolutely love it every time!
The restaurant itself isn’t anything fancy or big, but the food is heavenly and reasonably priced, relative to other Thai cuisine prices. 
Personal favourites are the Thai Fried Rice, Yellow Curry and Chicken with Cashew Nut. 
Seems to be very authentic and full of flavour. 
Can’t recommend this restaurant enough - best takeaway in the western suburbs xo
Great place! Tasty fresh carry, good size of portions. Absolutely good value for money. Not very spicy so answering the question about spice level I’d pick something hotter than I usually do.
Good Thai food at decent prices in Toowong. Friendly staff service. Has improved significantly under new management.
Some really tasty dishes - I especially like the Kao soi chicken and the drunken noodles. Some of their curries can be a little watery. Great prices though!
Good flavors. Tom yum was good and panang curry is creamy. Great value for money and I’ll come again to try more dishes.

After many years of intending to visit China Sea, we finally got around to it, and it was exceptional. We only wish we’d visited earlier. Not only was the food great, the service was wonderful as well. Highly recommend and can’t wait to go back.

It has been a wonderful dinner in a just perfect Chinese restaurant. food was delicious like usual, and service was efficient during a very busy nights. The dishes came a little bit slowly but it definitely worthy！！！
We had a large party for Chinese New, we enjoyed the great banquet, efficient service and lion dance! I will definitely be back again, Thank you!

Really enjoyable evening with excellent food. Three of us shared quail for entrée, then duck, Mongolian lamb, and mixed vegetables with tofu. We added Szechuan calamari – no room for desert. All the dishes we interesting and delicious.

I have eaten in many Chinese restaurants. China Sea is amongst the best, and very authentic Cantonese for a restaurant outside China. We have been coming back here a couple of times a year for many years, even before it moved from its old location in Fortitude Valley, and it has never disappointed. The quality of the food is consistently high. The service is friendly and efficient, even on our last visit just before Christmas when it was quite busy.
The dining atmosphere is better than most Chinese restaurants in Brisbane.

We came for dinner and it was excellent. 
We made reservations and we were not disappointed. It was so incredibly good and we are so full! You will not be dissatisfied in the meal or service! Be sure to make a reservation because this place gets easily crowded especially on weekends!
Best waiters ever! Full of historical facts about movie stars that have dined there. Food was phenomenal.  Bella 🤩
Food was great.   Bar tender was conversational and polite
The food is good and tasty! Had the red sauce pasta with shrimp and my sister got the chicken fettuccine, they use such big plate that makes the portion so little. Dessert was good too.
Best steak in town really enjoyed atmosphere service was great should make reservations

My wife and I have been eating at Rue De Paris since the late 90's and it is one of our favourite spots for Breakfast and Lunch.  The quality of the food is excellent and we are very picky people.  They have healthy options and supply Thick Wholemeal Bread which I love for Breakfast or a Club Sandwich and their Pouched Eggs are awesome.  We recommend Rue De Paris.
A nice venue with pleasant staff. The food for breakfast was good, well priced, and quick to arrive. Overall a good experience.
Excellent coffee and great staff, every single time...
Good food, though pricy. The location is the main downside, because it is a street cafe on Park Road, which is a very busy street. Every minute there is a truck rumbling by.
Pricey café food but typical of Park Rd fare.
Friendly staff. An interesting range of board games to play while you wait. Our pizza had a tasty and crispy crust but the pasta was so-so. Kinda empty for a Friday so vibe was missing.

Great kids experience - a fun little kids pack, lots of board games, and my one loved it. The friendly staff forgot my drinks order, my pizza was clearly a frozen base and a bit ordinary, but on the plus side the forgotten drinks order also was forgotten itself in the bill as well. I'm not sure it retains any of the charm (or food) of the original Kookaburra Cafe in Paddington, but even so, it's a welcome option.
Casual and relaxed. Beer on tap. Great service. Amazing pizzas.

Good pizza, good wine, and good music. Very family-friendly atmosphere, with an endless choice of board games. A good balance between kids and parents expectations for a delicious dining experience. Warmly suggested.
The supreme pizza is nice. Friendly and attentive staff.

This Indian restaurant is a safe bet for a great dining experience. It has a homely atmosphere. Terrific food and service. Deserves 5 stars, except that, despite requesting maximum 'Indian Hot' hot spiciness, the chef delivers on the side of safety.
Best indian restaurant in Brisbane. Authentic taste and consistently high standard (have been going here for years). Great service from a very nice owner and his team.

I have been going to this Indian restaurant for at least 20 years. I have never been unhappy with the food. The menu has a good cross section of dishes with meat and vegetarian selections. Love the vegetable curry and the Vindaloo curry.
Really nice food. Good variety of dishes. Quick when you want a takeaway. Friendly staff :)
Still the best Indian food around, has been that way for over 25 years

Staff here is very friendly and passionate to help us, and they always have the welcoming atmosphere. You can also enjoy events held by them such as a day trip to Sunshine coast. I feel really comfortable to seek help anytime. Any help? Go and see lovely staff
They are so kind. So I'm really happy to visit sol edu. If you have any problem, please visit to SOL Edu!

I really impressed about their services so I leave this review. 
 I have taken the English language schools for around 1 year in Brisbane. I always went with Sol edu when I signed up. 
The first impression of SOL agency is that they are ready to help all Internatinal students in Australia. They keep relationships with many language schools (I guess they keep relationships in almost all language schools in Brissie), moreover have lots of specials. I really got a lot of benefits thanks to that specials. Furthermore, all staffs in Sol edu are kind and have lots of experiences. I always hesitate before I make a decision but they waited instead of pressing me. All staffs already took many language schools and a lot of students have a relationships with them so they can recommend you depending on your circumstances.
 It must be the best choise if you were considering what angecy would you go.
This is the worst education agent in Brisbane.
There is very good for service and variety informations.

This place has great fish n chips! We go there most Sunday evenings. The food is always fresh and consistently well prepared and delicious; range of fresh salads; fish always well cooked. The chips especially are excellent - so many places have mediocre chips. Service is relaxed and friendly. Nick on front counter is efficient and friendly. Go there. Barry Young

From all the shops around this area, I picked this place to buy my mom a healthy meal. I ordered a grilled Barramundi with Chips for $18 and a small Salad for $7. Neither the fish, the portion size nor how it ended being soaking in oil was what I expected from paying a $25 for a meal. The take away paper bag didn't even have cutlery in it. Way below many other Fish & Chips experiences I had from a quality as well value for money.

We ordered the seafood platter for two, which was plenty for two adults and one toddler. The platter came with a choice of the salad. We had the crumbed hallumi and rocket leave, which was very nice too. 
The crumbs are fluffy and crunchy. The quality of the seafood are also fresh.
The staff is very friendly.
The service is a bit a slow. I noted that the dishes came out at the pace of 20 minutes or so. That’s probably they are freshly made on orders.

simply the best fish and chips by a long shot. You can easily tell from the first bite that  these guys are committed to keeping that delicious authentic classical fish and chips taste. It's worth every penny. Trever
Go here if you are on a diet. Excellent taste, but providing a decent share of chips is apparantly not hipster anymore.
Well priced, good size portions, tasty food, quick service. The place might not be most aesthetically pleasing but food outweighs it. The red curry and Pad Thai were fantastic.

Solid suburban asian food. BYO is a great option for having large gatherings (as the name suggests). Quick, tasty and relatively inexpensive food that hits the spot, good location in west end for more activity after dinner wraps up
Really delicious and very very quick food. The lemon chicken lacked a bit in flavour and the curry was spicy when I asked for mild. Nice atmosphere
Loved it very tucked away. Great menu.
Good service, prices reasonable, food was ok. Larb was not spicy

You can find many great Indonesian tastes in Shalom Brisbane. They have quite large range of varieties in the menu. You will get chicken, beef, duck and seafood dishes. Their Sambal sauce has great taste. You must try it if you are a spicy food lover. Thanks for your kind service.

Nice little Malay restaurant serving a solid range of dishes. My beef soup with chicken balls was lacking in flavour, but this was more than compensated for with the Beef Cha Cha which just fell off the bone with nice spices. Watch out for the dipping sauce - it has one hell of a kick to it!
Great little restaurant. Big meal sizes, beautiful fresh food, good service. 5 mains and 2 entrees was just over $70, so great value too.
Just an average indonesian restaurant. Service is fast. It's a small go to place for small groups.Only good thing is it's a halal food restaurant. Too much hot sauses with more or less same flavours.
Excellent place and food amazes my taste buds. Beautiful smile on every bite. Thanks for such a nice food
Thanks for providing such a delicious food. Service was fantastic and the staff was kind and friendly. Love to come here again.
Very small portions, overpriced food. Not impressed with the quality and taste.

Went there for lunch. Was pretty average. The place has been there for ages and is starting to look a little tired. The waitress was really nice and attentertive though. 

The dish is a little pricey given the presentation and food quality. The rice was overcooked and the papadum come half soggy as they're dunked in the curry. The curry had a strong vinagerette tang to it...which makes me think it is just chicken thrown in ready made simmer sauce. The menu said it comes with salad but in reality it's less than quarter of a grated carrot and a few spinach leaves.

Absolutely a waste of time.

I went in and ordered a chicken dish with garlic naan but ended up with raw chicken and not fully cooked naan. After mentioning my food to the waitress she took my chicken dish back to the kitchen they warmed it up a bit more and give it right back to me and said here you go so I tried it and I'm had random pieces they were raw and random pieces cooked. 

Neither the masala nor the curry were blended. It just tasted like a bowl of wrong with a side of raw garlic dough After paying for a meal I just left and went somewhere else to eat as I would rather pay more than be sick for Australia Day long weekend.

Wasted our $170/- on third grade preparations, they have no clue what they serving tandoori chicken was just boiled with salt and colour not even grilled, shame on you hire new chefs or stop wasting peoples money on such food which is not even close to Indian. One 1st jan 2019 it was closed as we were craving we went back on 3rd jan 19 and spare me the horror we ordered rogan josh, chicken korma and TANDOORI CHICKEN we could not have food roti was dry taste was horrendous and tandoori chicken was a joke. Please shut down if you keep serving such food because its a shame sitting on a prime location of Brisbane. Portions are joke.

2 star review is for the service. I had dined there a few times and had been wanting to take my partner there. I purchased a voucher from Living Social for their 5 course Discovery Menu. Upon arrival, we were referred to as the 'Living Social Table' and were seated at a table right against the front door and a wall. The table and chairs were on a slope. The table was wobbling and I had to constant adjusting my chair to stop it from sliding. 

After expressing my dissatisfaction to the Manager we were moved to a different table. However, it has ruined the fine dining experience. 

In all fairness, I would give the food 4 stars. However, I still would not return again as Tukka treats customers with a coupon as second class customers.

My favourite restaurant in Brisbane - a truly unique and high-quality dining experience of true Australian food.  Highly recommend for a special occasion or if you have guests from overseas.  Prices are what you would expect for a high-end restaurant but absolutely worth it, matched with excellent service.  Fantastic selection of Australian wines and beers to match the menu.  Highlight is the Native Platter, which is brilliant.
Amazing food native Australia ingredients

I haven't been to Tukka for over a year and I've got to say it was still excellent. The whole team did a wonderful job and it's every bit as good as I remembered! The menu is based around the same concept, but they have continued to evolve the cuisine and the flavours were fresh, creative and most importantly, delicious! We booked for a work function and we will definitely return. We were afforded the full menu to choose from and the service team took the time to take the new comers to Tukka through the different flavours, berries, herbs and meats on offer. Thanks so much Tukka and we look forward to next time!

Tried the degustation and experienced mixed results. I enjoyed he candied native fruits and the cheese platter. The kangaroo was well cooked but was missing direction, as it was just a meaty taste. The crocodile dishes could have had a stronger flavour, and the uncooked (citrus cured) entree version didn't sit well with any of our group (one ended up being sick).

To be honest food is delicious dan great value for money. We really enjoy their beef and dried noodles though. On my first visited it is awesome experience but this time seems like they didn’t maintenance their place really well. Floor was very dirty seems like never swept and flies everywhere. If outside was like this I was wondering how’s about in the back. I recommend this place to my bf but when we were there he said “you will get sick when you eat on dirty place like this”. I hope the owner can maintain restaurant better so customer would be happy to come back because food is really delicious just poorly maintained.

Trang is honestly the best value for money Vietnamese restaurant in Brisbane. I have eaten there over 10 times and the food is always incredible, especially considering the reasonable pricing. Staff are always so friendly and welcoming. Highly recommend the Laksa.

My favorite Viet restaurant in town!! Love all of their menu. I have probably been there 1 - 2 times a month for last 8 years. Whatever I chose from their menu, I was always satisfied. Friendly staffs and fast serving as well.
Great selection. Strangely the take away has been more impressive than eating in. Kinda conflicted but the food is nice.
Place is usually really good, today I waited 40 min for crispy chicken. To get a soggy cold piece of chicken. Very disappointed.

Salad days! Lettuce reflect... 

This is my regular "go to" place for lunch or a morning coffee. 

Ram' and Mercedes make a fabulous brew, while Barb and Carol create refreshingly delicious fruit smoothies and healthy salads. 
The portions are generous as are their smiles. 

Soy leads the team, always positive and happy. You can tell the staff are a coherent bunch; it shows in their fresh approach to customer service. 

The food is tasty, fresh and fast. They take pride in their work and products. 

Superb service! Respect to the crew at BLB Baguette Bar. I've only had one baguette and it was a meal indeed. If you're hungry, go grab yourself a baguette. 

The indoor / outdoor setting is sunny, so too are the dispositions of the staff. 

PS: Order a coffee and get a free piece of toast with a condiment of your choice. The secret is out! Great service and tasty food triumph.

My recent experiences at Blue Lemon was very pleasant. The staff are lovely, food arrived quick and tasted amazing and had great quality. It  was also a great value for money. Definitely coming back for another round.
Sandwiches? Delicious. Prices? Affordable. The ladies behind the counter? Angels.
Had an amazing lunch here.Great food and reasonably priced,relaxed atmosphere,very friendly and professional staff.Had a great time,will be back again!!
Really good spot for a quick lunch of salad or a sandwich. Order at the counter and then there is indoor and outdoor seating.
Excellent afternoon spent with good friends. Delicious BBQ, cold frosty beers. Good crowd of folks enjoying family and friends. For over 30 years I have always enjoyed a BBQ at the Creek. Love it.

Absolutely beautiful meal. Short wait even though it was busy. Great atmosphere inside and outdoors. Staff are so lovely,friendly. ..live music was amazing, great talent. Can't wait to come back for another meal!!

Great heritage listed pub with lots of character. One of the few pubs where you can order beer 'off the wood' (wooden keg). Good food. Great selection of good quality steaks. Large big screen for watching sport.

Seafood spaghetti was great but way too much pasta. 100 day aged steak was stunning cooked perfectly. The baked potato need sour cream. Can't wait to come back and get some oysters as there was none on the menu. Otherwise would have given 5 stars.

Very disappointed. The staff were great, as was the service. But the price you pay for their steaks... You excited them to be cooked to perfection and taste amazing. However, 1 person at our table of 6 ended up getting a steak cooked the way they asked for it.

This place is amazing. Fantastic food. Family owned, friendly, welcoming and accommodating. They're a regular part of our take out rotation and we love it. But even better if you can done in.

Must have garlic bread. Might be the only take out garlic bread I like at this stage, because they use actual garlic and butter. So decadent! Follow their social media for specials.
Pasta out of a packet. The sauce was just crushed tomato from a can. The service was friendly and there are board games on offer but it didn't make up for the terrible pasta. Won't be back.

The pizza is amazing, the pasta is amazing, the atmosphere is amazing BUT the service is even more amazing!!! 
You definitely need to add this to your list of places to eat 😋 I love it here and I especially love the monthly bike night - keep it up guys!!
Always a pleasure. Kids and us love the place because you get what you pay for and the pizza is super tasty and not full of rubbish like the cheap places. Really good.
Healtier wholemeal bases but still full of flavour and really reasonable prices.

Good range of books and an ambience to indulge in thumbing the eye catching titles, with a good spread of gadgetry and toys. Surprising to see decline in the range offered in diaries and calendars while a rise in generic stationary items. Highly trending in non fiction titles is another aspect of 2019 at landmark books arena.. Very encouraging changes in layout of stores, so that one feels like spending time there.

One of the best places to go to if you're a person who just loves spending your time amongst books. They have the perfect collection of books.. books of all categories.. also a comic book haven for comic book fans. They have a dedicated section when people can read books too. 
Apart from books, they have a wide collection of toys for children as well as action figures for collectibles and enthusiasts. 
Fashion accessories, unique forms of diaries, office supplies, bags, mugs, and chocolates are some of the other things that can be found here.

I had been to Landmark which is in Forum, it has developed over a timeframe as far as inside and quality also. Milestone is one stop arrangement on the off chance that you are a book significant other. You have all the assortment of books running from anecdotal, magazines, recorded, instructive and so forth. They have great assortment of books for children too, I like the flawless story books for them.

The games activity is likewise great and contains all the fundamental necessities for all the game. We had purchased a cycle from that point, the conveyance for which was entirely quick. A dazzling spot for book significant others.

Nice place to find books..... And you also get cute stuffs... Not to mention the toy section.... Oh boy!!! .... Doesn't matter how old I get, I will always go in there to check out those cute stuffed toys and marvel avenger figures!!

The shop is good. The collection of books and games is good ( online price is much cheaper). But the staff is untrained. They asked me debit card pin stating ATM machine under charging instead of asking cash as alternative. They did not serviced me to another queue for payment. The payment processing takes more than 30 minutes in queue. Very slow staff.

Never again!!

Delivery took more than 2 hours.
The "groentenmix" suppose to be tempura vegetables, but contained prawn tempura (my wife is allergic to it) and there was a hair in the Yaki Udong Tori Teriyaki.....

All in all a real disappointment.
Super lekkere sushi, zowel om af te halen of om thuis te laten bezorgen. Regelmatig wat besteld altijd goed. Ze zijn snel!

Wij bestellen, of halen altijd af bij sakura als we thuis sushi gaan eten. Elke keer opnieuw weer top service. Sushi smaakt ons elke keer weer voortreffelijk en altijd z'n 45 min bezorgtijd. Zelfs vandaag op 2e kerstdag, wanneer er iets mis ging met onze bestelling, kregen we netjes een nieuw product. (Terwijl dit niet nodig was!) Het is dat ik nooit cash in huis heb, anders had ik zeker wat fooi als bedankje erbij gedaan! (Sorry daarvoor 🙈) Tot de volgende bestelling :)
Goede sushi kwaliteit. Stond op tijd klaar. Minpunt dat een blikje drinken niet was meegeleverd.
De beste sushi van Apeldoorn en heel veel keus in wat je wilt eten. Komen wel altijd later bezorgen dan je besteld en dat is wel teleurstellend. Maar heerlijk!
Good veg food

Never ever try this restro,  this is a fake address amazingly no phone number and no street name. 
Very bad experience waste my time to visit this.
nice meals!

Where do I begin. My overall experience here this morning was absolutely outstanding! The coffee was superb, my breakfast meal was extremely tasty and the service was impeccable! I highly recommend The Gunshop Cafe to all who enjoy a lovely sit down brekky and/or coffee. The courtyard at the rear of the cafe is a great place to relax with friends.

Lovely old house/shop converted into this very popular cafe, with an indoor area and an outdoor covered seating area. There is a pleasant relaxed environment here making it perfect for a weekend brekky or lunch. There are some really nice food options that differ from many cafes offering generic options. You can certainly get classic favourites, but there is variety. The meals are very tasty! The milkshakes/smoothies are delicious and so is the coffee. Very good service!
This place is amazing. Incredible breakfast options and great coffee. Highly recommended!?

My breakfast of poached eggs and  greens with dukkah was excellent, as was my husband's sausage with bubble and squeak, but it took an hour for our food to come and no one noticed until we asked. Maybe it was just a busy Saturday.we wouldn't have minded the wait if we had felt looked after. Such a shame.
Love this place. Perfect in ever way. Kudos to the owners and staff for a nicely balanced place and great menu.

I've, sadly-due to work and timings, only visited this shop twice but as an amateur cigar and coffee aficionado I will unfailingly offer my personal credit to this shop. Great cigars and coffee- enjoyed out on the balcony while watching the world go by- a great way to achieve some time to one's self appreciating the smaller things in life.
Really cool vibe. Love enjoying a coffee on the rooftop terrace. Great selection of cigars on offer and very good coffee.
Incredible service! Very rare to find a man so passionate about his craft and so friendly
Unique looks, great coffee, amazing proprietor once you penetrate his gruff exterior-- that's just a test. Be interesting and interested and find that Phil is a great guy.
Simply the best coffee I've ever had, and probably ever will have.

As soon as you walk in the ambiance of the place is so inviting. It is hard to get a seat at times but that reflects the popularity of the place. The good and coffee is always good and the staff, although busy, are always friendly. Love this place.

Great coffee. Great food. Great ambience. Go upstairs or down the back for a surprise meal. This is a wonderful place to relax after shopping or a visit to the medical centre. Parking is easy if you use Coles for their 2 hour free underground car parking. Just pop in after coffee and buy a bunch of flowers to please that loved one, and get your parking ticket validated. Don't forget to thank the women for their friendly service. It has a restroom if you are caught.

This is exactly the kind of place I love. Cosy, quirky, and a lovely, relaxed atmosphere. My girlfriend took me here for breakfast as she'd visited a couple of times before and really enjoyed it. I'm so glad she did. We had a lovely meal, and rounded it off with a raspberry cheesecake which was just delicious. I only wish I'd had time on my short holiday to make a repeat visit. If I ever return to Brisbane it's definitely on my must-do list.

I love this place. It’s got like 17 kinds of cheesecake and the decore is like being in Bali or something! It’s so cruisy I could stay there all day and the staff are just lovely. Very well priced meals as well! Open practically all the time! Just awesome.

One of the best little Cafes in Brisbane. Not too busy but always bustling. Excellent food which is not to expensive. Easily the best atmosphere of any cafe I’ve ever been to. Seating options for 1-10 people both inside and out. Clearly it is a cultural centre for West End where many people meet for clubs and associations but this doesn’t ruin the atmosphere. Can’t recommend it highly enough. (Also great date location with lots to see in West End and Southbank before finishing the date at the Three Monkeys with a drink and some Turkish delight)

Amazing cocktails and great vibe. Only thing that needs to be changed is the booths. The booth chairs are so long and close to the table you need to slide in and it's uncomfortable. Service was fabulous!

Lovely to see the Asahi Rep who I see at my work at the Fox Hotel in at the Lychee Lounge when I arrived tonight.  I was greatly Honoured by Vicki the proprietor of the Lychee Lounge, who asked me to participate in tasting some exquisite Japanese Whiskey. Excellent smooth whiskey mellow and seeing Josh and Alex who have perfected the Best Espresso Martinis in Brisbane. If you have not visited this quaint cocktail lounge take it from an old school chef  this is truly a blessing to find in the South Brisbane and West End district. I urge you to make an effort to acquaint yourself with this delightful place, the ambience is sublimely perfect the choice to kick off a night with a paramour or to end an evening with close friends. Whatever fits your mood but I urge you to please visit this place. I can guarantee you will not be dissapointed.

Hosted my birthday party here one year. Great communication. Minimum spend to reserve an area but you get to spend it on food and drinks there. Winning. Cool vibe. Good selection of drinks. Recommend.

Cozy cocktails.

Don't be fooled by the small space, the Lychee Lounge packs a punch when it comes to cocktails. There excellent menu will suit all tastes and they always have a full complement of the classics. The staff were friendly and if you're there with just two or three people then a seat at the bar provides plenty of entertainment as your (and everyone else's) cocktails get made.

I'm not sure anyone who goes to a cocktail lounge worries about price, but just to note for those frugal people out there, don't expect much change out of a 20 for each drink.
absolutely impeccable service, greeted by a friendly face and a very warm welcome. 10/10 would recommend
Highly recommend this place for creative coffee and brunch options

Service is alright. I always see a lot of people at this place. I decided to try it because it looked interesting. The coffee is decent however the food is quite scarce for the price (not that pricey but still). The avocado on toast I ordered still needed to be mashed and the presentation was lacking.
It was really average and quite lazily presented.
Exceptional coffee. Strong & smooth and perfect temperature. Really great space too.
Great coffee, simple and tasty menu bigger tables available at rear good place to work on computer

Just moved to working in the area and went in for a coffee. Looks great on the outside, inside  is full of character. Met Adrian the owner yesterday and he remembered my name today. Had a bite to eat and coffee today, both were delicious. Thanks Adrian, I have new work local.

Of the 5 meals that came out 4 were excellent. The steaks were excellent, and the slaw topped with crispy string potatoes amazing.The only disappointing one was the paella. The prawns were dry and it tasted as if there was a tin of tomatoes dumped on top and that was about it.

Great food and excellent drinks list. The tap beer menu could do with a bit more variety, even with the limited number of taps. The bottled menu made up for it though. The service was fast and efficient but not that personable. The food was fantastic.
Excellent - laid back but classy. Mid week dinner specials are nice but small- - but fairly priced. You can have a relqxed conversation or meeting here no troubles.
Great starter, Butchers block, went for the small plate so we could have some mains but would go the large starter next time, it was so good!

Very disappointed, I'm not sure if they ware understaffed tonight but we waited 40 minutes for our Arancini starter and then another half hour for our mains (only a table for 2). Given there ware maybe 5 other tables seated at the time I don't really see how that's reasonable. Furthermore, our mains ware just plain awful, the lamb shanks ware bland, had no sauce, the mash had an excessive amount of truffle oil and the asparagus had no seasoning; The pork belly was cooked to a crisp to the point where i couldn't distinguish between the meat and the crackling and the center was just pure rendered fat, and the "candied walnuts" ware really just plain walnuts and they ware so stale they seemed to have been left in an open container for a week over the kitchen bench before being used.

If you're in the area just head next door to Zero Fox, you'll be much better off.

This is a great little secluded spot for a nice sit down meal and a coffee. In the mornings it's not too busy and staff are friendly. Apparently it's also great for lunch and evening drinks but I've only been for breakfast.
A niche little hole with some of the best coffee, atmosphere and service around. Definitely great for dates or small groups. Does lack space but more than makes up for it

Big call I know, but the Brew Burger (beef brisket) is the best burger I've every had. I go back time and time again and it never disappoints. The truffle fries with kewpie mayo are a fine accompaniment. There's probably other good stuff on the menu too but I can't go past it.

I don't write reviews but I want them to know that the service is bad. I got recommended this place by my sister as I'm here in Brisbane for the first time.
As soon as I arrived I came here to have lunch.

The thing is the staff is unfriendly when they serve my meal they juat dropped it on my table. I said thank you but the lady didn't even look at me or said anything. 
Literally just dropped the food and gone.

스태프 엄청 불친절해요.
추천 받고 왔는데 브리즈번 오자마자 기분 망쳤네요.
The Beef Brisket burger was amazing. Great flavors and a good size. Added bonus of only $10 on a Monday night. A must if visiting Brisbane

Tucked away at the back of a building this place is a hidden gem which I have recently discovered. The coffee is amazing. The hot chocolate is awesome too made with real chocolate and so many different flavours. Would love it if there was more seating available through as it fills up at busy times and not very suitable for larger groups.

This is the best coffee shop in Brisbane! Would not go anywhere else for coffee as they cannot compete with John Mills Himself friendly staff, great atmosphere and most importantly the best tasting coffee! Their treats are also fantastic there’s nothing like a chocolate brownie or a raspberry blondie to go with a great brew! 

 Keep up the great work John Mills!!
Love the coffee and the speed. Staff are friendly  as well. The food looks good but i haven't consumed any thing yet from this coffee shop.
Amaaaaaazing everything. Try their gorgeous range of hot chocolates. A great place to buy beans for your home coffee brew, lovely spot with great staff.

A hidden gem in the bottom of a building on Charlotte St (down the stairs and right at the giant koala), or down a laneway off Elizabeth St. Tight space if you're dining in but great quality coffee and lovely friendly service. I eyed off the treat cabinet but didn't get any. They looked delicious.

Incredible food! Only regret I didn't take photos of it. Would definitely be heading back there to work my way through the menu. If you're tired of eating the same cafe food every day, this is the place to go. Lovely staff as well.

Great service. Delicious food. Cute spot. I had the French toast with bacon and it was quite sweet but tasty. Everyone else at my table enjoyed their choice and the coffee was great as usual. It can get a little noisy but most places are these days.

Anouk is almost an institution in Paddington at this point. 
Menu gets updated regularly so there's often something new to try. 
Accommodate dietary needs. 
It's always quite busy, and they don't take bookings after 830am. 
Wait staff aren't always the nicest. 
The owner will have a chat.
I love this space! Comfy bench couch thing and lots of pants. The team at Anouk are fun and quirky and always provide great service. My favourite cafe in Paddington! Keep up the great work guys!
Amazing food. Best coffee in town. And most importantly amazing service. Couldn’t ask for a better place for brunch in Brisbane.

An excellent music venue for live bands & a place to rub shoulders with other performing artists after their own gigs! Great breakfasts & meals all round! Wheelchair access is available & their own restroom! A great event venue!

The bartender painstakingly made me a really delicious cocktail last night, he even hand squeezed the lemon juice ❤️ Always a great time here. Go explore the out back seat in area, decorated with a beautiful mural, string lights and a.. washing line? If it’s your thing like mine, you’ll love it.
Great place to see musical acts. The front Bar is cosy and great to feel immersed in the music. The back room is more spacious and relaxed.

Love rics!
Best place to chill with a Delicious cocktail and a cigarette in your hand , whilst sitting in their backyard ♡

Absolutely awful management. The manager there with the big nose needs to stop being so power hungry and starting fights with patrons. Never have I been treated so disgustingly by someone. The place would improve immensely if she was fired, it's long overdue and word of mouth spreads.
